# JavaScript Function Basics

```javascript
// Function declaration
function greet(name) {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}

// Function usage
const message = greet('World');
console.log(message);
```

### Components of a Function:

| Component   | Description                                 |
|-------------|---------------------------------------------|
| Declaration | The process of defining a function.          |
| Parameters  | Inputs to the function.                      |
| Return      | Output from the function.                    |

> **Note:** Functions encapsulate code for reusability and readability.

# Types of JavaScript Functions

```javascript
// Regular Function
function add(a, b) {
    return a + b;
}

// Arrow Function
const multiply = (x, y) => x * y;

// Anonymous Function
setTimeout(function() {
    console.log('This is an anonymous function!');
}, 1000);
```

